orig_text: The testimonies are somewhere in the Archives. Search through their records and see if you can't find them.
What is taking so long? Move closer guys!
All of you need to be inside the dealership so I can blow up the C4!
Awesome! With all those bags, the trade should be smooth.
I'm leaving in half a minute!
Ahh... ok. We're sending some guys over to sweep the area, just in case.
Don't shoot please don't shoot.
OK guys, get inside and locate the art. We want the paintings with the red stickers on. Look out for guards and cameras.
The van is coming back. Get ready!
4 paintings, not much, but we'll take it.
This district matches with... Hmmm, give me some more time...
They're inside!
Blood coming out your ears fucker!
Outstanding. We're almost done - now get to the escape. Just stay with the blue containers!
Come on guys! Get inside now!
Woops. That one's on me I assume.
Take'em out.
The vault is open. Get in there. Finish him. The Dentist is watching.
What was that room again?
Ah, my work is pretty dull. Repetitive. Like a machine. But it pays well.
I'm like goddamn Santa Claus here.
Gang, you still need to blow up that radar.
Gonna cut you inte pieces!
They shot me, but it's only a minor one. Barely hurts.
Hold them back, I'm looking for an escape driver as we speak!
You gotta clear the street!
Heads up, they're deploying tactical squads on a nearby roof top.
And that's the whole delivery...
The ladders are a weakpoint. Don't let the cops get up them.
Keep moving and don't play around. You trigger the alarm, we're screwed.
My money comes from... well, a sort of trust fund. I'd let you in...but I don't trust you.
Let's get to the docks!
Bag up the loot - gold is heavy remember - and wait for me to send the escape car. Clear? Oh - my guy left the thermal drill to get into the vault out back. Let's roll.
... just hang on!
You should be able to hold your ground inside the park.
OK, you go to the harbor like we planned. Offload the coke from the pick-up. You'll need to signal Hector's boat in the warehouse to get him to come in.
And... yes, that is a satisfactory piece of business! All of the bags! Now, please, attach yourselves to the cables, join me up here and let us meet in person!
It's done. Now hit the button, and lower the bollards.
OK we're good to go. I'll get you guys cleared to the safe house. Their arsenal is gone. Their soldiers toothless.
Great, you found some thermite. Now we can melt our way through that steel gate.
Hey, over here!
Trash the entire mall. Either destroy each store individually, or look for something to torch them all.
Almost there.
Looks like we are doing this loud, gents! The panic room's locked down so we do this the hard way. Bile will get us a thermal lance. Hang on.
More snipers!
I'm gonna kill you!
There's two cans of thermite there. One of you other guys grab it.
I don't like it... Let's get this over with as soon as we can, get the paintings on the table.
So that's where that Russian rat is holed up. Get yourselves and any loot back to the car. Hmm, those crates got me thinking...
You have to take the snipers out. I'm stuck here!
The Armory! Safely locked up, but spend a keycard and it should open up.
Looks like they're setting up snipers on nearby rooftops. Keep your eyes open!
Don't make me whip you like a government mule. Get on the Intercom.
What the hell! Come back here!
We'll take what you have.

Vlad's brother-in-law hid from the cops in the mall's loading bay. It seems he hid the coke in various boxes, boxes that have now been distributed to shops all over the mall. He also disguised himself in a Santa Claus costume and stole some vodka and got drunk. What a mess. The cops got suspicious of the drunk Santa and apprehended him. You'll need to free him and ask him if he remembers what boxes he put the coke in.
There are snipers on the surrounding buildings.
You're going to have DC's finest crawling up your ass. Cops on the scene.
Two blocks away!
I'll get you some nice Christmas presents if you solve this thing for me.
Hurry the fuck up!
You guys ready? This is where you get out.
Da. Heard one talking about clowns. What madness.
Right now you are succeeding.
Alright, fuck it...
Come on, gang. Find a blowtorch.
Helicopters landing. Load up the engine and hope it is the one.
That's survellance dealt with. You don't need to stress over the cameras anymore.
Look like the power is back, gang.
Grab Dentists' loot. That's what we came for.
He's dead. Good riddance. Chopper's on the way, guys. Dentist sent a few bottles of champagne with it. Sure Hoxton will be grateful too. Good work.
You don't wanna go back to prison, right?
Remember, we're here to rob a bank. If some election equipment gets destroyed in the process, that's too bad. And it would be a real shame if the voting results became unusable somehow...
Drones with cameras, really? Murkywater are stepping up their game. Be careful that you don't get spotted.
We've got your money right here. The info is in the safe. I'll open it. No funny shit or you die.
We got eight!
Chopper is back guys!
Whenever you're ready, I want you on the roof, then we'll get you outta there with the zipline.
If there were more crews like you I think the world would need to store its valuables elsewhere.
You see it? Water fuckin' running down the wall. Totally fucked!
OK, we go loud! That panic room is secure, so you'll need a thermal lance to get through. It's on the way.
Put the delivery in the car...
Damn, they rigged the boxes with C4! Defuse them!
Put them down!
Excellent work, gang! Absolutely amazing. But now you need to get out of there before the place collapses.
Keep them off the routers.
OK, people! One more bag - we just need one more bag to satisfy Hector.
It's the Hondurans! They fucking followed us! Shit!
... then, we'll trade.
The wheelman had to run, too hot. He's relocating.
Thats him! Dont let him escape!
I'm coming in - don't know what dock though!
Put all the wares in the car!
I gotta go in two minutes.

To bypass the security system and get into the vault, patch the devices you have directly into the two control boxes, they should be around there somewhere. Then I'll hack in remotely and do the rest.
Don't you just love science? Great team effort. We've retired the engine until... Well until we decide to liberate it ourselves. Enjoy the PAYDAY.
... this is fine, we'll take it.
Wonder what's in the case. Could be The Butcher's explosives. Have a look.
Ok guys, go across the roof!
There's no easy way out for the tree. We'll have to take the glass roof off the mall. Signal Bile with a flare and he'll drop a little present for you. Yeah, C4.
Just wait there, you'll be picked up soon. I promise!
Great job getting the GPS in place in the truck. We're gonna do this next job in daylight. It'll look like a takedown.
Don't take stupid risks. These guys are dangerous!
... keep cool!
OK, OK, I'm done with the security hack, everything's unlocked.
One more time
And....lift off! Outstanding work, crew!
Watch out for those bags now!
Crane's over here. Can be positioned over the main hall skylight.
Alright, bring it to the van, it's right across the street.
Happy birthday. Vault full of freshly loaded safe deposit boxes. Who's in?
I'll be there in 30 seconds.
I'm there in one minute...
I'll tell you what. We were never gonna deal with you guys! We'll take it all!
You found it. Good! Good. I knew I could depend on you.
Alright, you got it. Let's get out of here!
The chopper is fully loaded. Wait for it to come back.
13 to go.
Don't forget the bags.
That's an attack helicopter incoming! Hold on to your hats!
A little hickup; there's a server missing in here. Log says it was taken to the IT Department for maintenance. We need that server, so you'll have to retrieve it.
You got nothing? You guys are killing me!
You need to cover me while open the gate!
Check the roof - find your route inside. Get creative, we don't have time.
We stole this from a lab not a million miles from here. Two hundred thirty eight thousand six hundred and six miles, to be precise.
...Plan is as follows.
What's going on down there? You staying alert?
Fires' out. You did well, gang.
No time to brew coffee for that pissed old fart. Keep him safe. I'm sending an extraction now.
Hey, there he is. Looks like he's by the pools.
You can't touch me! I got protection!
Great, now you just need to find the second one.
Bang on target, gang!
I lost connection, I need you to get the power back.
Great. Now place that C4 and we can start getting out of this place.
Well, you partially opened the panic room anyway. That means the thermal lance will be quicker!
That's it, gang. Now get back to the trains and get your hands on the EMP bomb.
Nice work! I gave the pilot the word to get you to the docks because you aren't done yet.
Tackle ready?
That's the alarm. Alright, weapons hot! Don't worry about the Moretta. She's moving and is gonna keep moving.
Hector was the traitor! He tried to set us up as a part of the Rats job. No wonder the cops found the meth lab so fast. All along, he was the fucking rat.
Recon the bank. My guy dropped a thermal lance somewhere on the premises... Around the back of the bank, find it.
Where's that laptop? Found it yet?
Drop dead, Boris.
Flying fast as a shark.
No no, there's no need for that.
Be careful going in...
Alarm is off. Smooth. Open the door!
No more! There's no more room!
We're taking the train - grab the zipline up to the bridge!
Follow Bile so he can pick you up in a safer spot! Don't forget Roscoe!
Place the missiles by the radar and activate them. That should do the trick.
No!
You damn asshole bastards. I'll fucking kill you for this. You hear? Kill you!
I'll be there in 3 minutes.
Guys, break the windows so I can send down the ladder, over.
Nice. Scoop that loot up quickly. Let's get out of here before they notice.
Well fuck me sideways - it's the motherfucking PAYDAY gang!
Alarm boxes identified. Go and disrupt them for me.
Mask up when you're ready to roll.
They must have tailed us from the scene!
Oh fuck me sideways man!
Copy that, In holding pattern til you give clearance.
We need to add ephedrine tablets to start the cooking process. Find some and add it into the mixer.
The convoy's stopped, move toward the bus.
Here's Johnny!
I think they are all dead. Thanks to you, my friends.
That's the time lock done. Try and keep the sneak going. Now, the vault has a three step clearance control. The first I've already taken care of. Just head there and use the fingerprint scanner.
Good, now do your little magic on that baby. Get the pick-up running!
Time to move! The escape vehicle is parked near the main entrance!

OK, the thermal drill you need for the vault is somewhere in the parking lot. Get it before you do your takedown. Then you can go hit that vault. Watch for cameras and bank employees. Do your homework before you go in and remember cash is king.
It's open! Get the stuff out of the deposit boxes!
The Mendoza cartel just got knocked on its ass. Nothing hurts like taking a financial beating and they just took a big one. Hector will rise and that's good fortune for us down the line.
Damn! The cops have the mall locked down. So we're getting you out by air. Light a flare for the chopper.
We're leaving!
Now you get paid!
Your wheelman didn't lose the tail! Goddammit!
Every now and then, just don't trust me, guys.
Ok, go pick up the C4 and then plant it right above the panic room.
Gambling is a disease. Stop while you can, sucker!
Thankfully, I have a supply of C4 right here.
Heads up, sniper team just set up on a nearby building.
OK, I'm in his system. Lab will open shortly.
I got to rush out of here!
Oh, put some sleeping gas in there too. Don't leave it behind.
Dropping this one at the silo!
Their databases are partitioned across two servers. Downloading the first one now.
Over here!
All yours for the price of... say... 18 bucks.
Just like St Nazaire!
The escape vehicle is leaving in nine minutes.
What is taking you so long?...
Look in the boxes, gang!
Good luck on your treasure hunt, guys. And remember, keep it quiet.
Hit the Crime.net station to get out of here.
You got all of 'em? Ha!
Coming in, guys.
... Put the product in the car...
Cage is right where I put it. Like fucking 633 Squadron!
Make sure you grab an extra body bag. My treat this time.
Kill 'em!
Arriving in two...
I'll tell you what. We were never gonna deal with you guys! We'll take it all!
No more party people, they're all heading out.
We agreed to get these damn caches for Hector.
Gang, that's a heavy SWAT van that just rocked up. Be ready.
Security looks pretty tight at the front. Maybe look for other ways in.
Ok! Get the briefcase!
The financial world has never been healthier! We only laid off ten employees in the last day.
It's fine, we'll settle for this.
Two minutes. Learn to drive, asshole.
That's all of them.
One, two, cops are coming for you...
This place is for staff only. Offices can be accessed here.
Please, everyone into the airlock. The doors are designed so that the inner cannot open until the outer is closed.
The hack was interrupted. Get it going again.
There's a ladder leading to the roof. Over the garage.
Vault is open. New plan. Just stroll in and get to work. Easy money!
Only way back is forward, people!
Throw the loot into the tree!
We've got the engine, I'll have my guy here inspect it.
They've got a PR office here. Maybe we should have one of those. They probably have a laptop.
Into the dockyard, gang. Keep an eye out for security and cameras. Go.
You can't let that bastard get away!
Come on! Fuck 'em up!
This is the last show of the greatest tour on Earth. Don't screw the pooch now.
We need a keycard to get into the prison. But where can we get one?
Phone's ringing, time to pick it up and start this trade off.
Another twelve and we're done.
I gotta keep moving so they don't get me!
Lasers in front of the vault. Let's shut them down.
Are the saws still running?
This is an effective way of gaining entry.
That's it, open it up.
Guys, search the spot where you landed. Bile has dropped some explosives for you.
Oh shit! This wasn't the deal! We are outta here!
Ten seconds now!
We've been expecting you fuckers!
Real close now.
Six left!
Excellent, you got the explosives. Now, plant them on the radar.
You're in. Next step is to get inside the mansion. But watch out - all the doors and windows are tied to an alarm.
Today could've been better, guys. But we'll have to deal with Locke eventually. He'll be running from more people than us.
Gang, ignite the tires. Give that chopper a nice thick smokescreen to worry about!
Head to the pyro booth. Top floor. Hurry!
Ralph Garnet has thelast piece of the puzzle. Find him and take his keycard. He's around there somewhere.
Eight
Listen to my lips....no!
He didn't pick up the server.
Please, leave the charges at the door, my friends.
Okay. The controls. Hack 'em, and keep the cops off.
Someone got away.
... you don't think our time's important?
We need to deal with the metal detectors. Best way: simply kill the power. There are electricity boxes around.
OK! We got some real scandal stuff here. He sold government arms to a rogue state - got paid in gold. The Democrats aint gonna like this.
What the hell? That's the wrong elevator. Hold on.
Ouch - that sure drew attention.
Remember we need both the Taxman and the server, people. Scare him and make him go into the limo once we've confirmed that he has the server on him.
Okay, lining up on the road. Gonna drop the cage there.
And... bam!
This whole scenario is just too familiar.
Cops are going for the balloon! Stop them!
Locke wants us to sabotage the radars. Better get to it.
That's the second stash. Two to go!
Hit the left and the middle.
Now top up his glass. Soon as he swallows, well, let's say he's going to go loud. Follow him, and get the card for his room.
Bile will be back soon. Hold on my friends!
Branch bank job with a twist, and the twist is golden. Bars, that is. Let's do our thing.
I'm betting it's in their safe.
The escape vehicle is leaving in seven minutes.
That was some damn good sneaking, Dallas. I am impressed.
Who the hell can do what we just did? No one! This will go down in history, just like I said.
Great job. Now get in the car and let's end this. Or hang around and really clean the joint.
Guys, patch into the radio. Let me speak to the Moretta.
It landed on flames... That can't be good.
Okay, think the bridge is looking good for a drop point.
Are we agreed upon this?
There's space between the trains too. It's worth a look.
People will pay fortunes for this ancient Babylonian shit.
They saw the broken window!
Give up and we will negotiate.
Barbarians are what you are! Barbarians!
They got Eddie! You'll have to continue on foot.
Sorry fellas, too slow - the getaway just left along with your freedom, look me up when you get out.
OK, that was some serious crawling around you guys did. Money secured though. I'll send a team to clean up. You stay low.
Just the guys we've been waiting for!
Whose bright idea was it to set up a methlab in an unventilated tin box?
Jump out like a jack-in-the-box. Masks on!
I'm glad you showed up! As you can see, I need some help here.
OK, we've got what we need. Time to get out of there.
Search those crates. Should be some C4 in one of them.
It's soooooo damned quiet...
Hey, we don't have all day!
The middle one, guys!
Hear that? That's C4! They're making entries!
This ventilation system could be used to our advantage, you know, to hide a body or transfer some of the extra through.
The police is on our back like a fucking pony tail!
Military blueprints in a high security transport? I'll see what I can find.
The escape van is ready, go when you're good!
Have you tried Robert's?
Holy fuck!
Don't go to the neighbours.
Broadsword calling Danny Boy. Deploy the skyhook, our boys are waiting. Over.
Police en route - coming in fast!
Abraham Lincoln once said: Give me six hours to chop down a tree and I will spend the first four sharpening the axe. He knew the importance of preparation.
This has to be the most persistent fucking cops I've ever seen!
Get that body over to the scanner.
Defend Hoxton. If you have cards, you can seal off the entrances.

Superb. The cash is loaded on pallets, which are secured to the deck. Only the logistics officer can release them, and his controls are up above you - you see? To access them, you must get to the stairs at the front of the aircraft, and then return this way.
Gang, find gas and ignite the tires. Give that chopper a nice thick smokescreen to worry about!
Jesus, the devastation....with you in 3.
The vault's open. Time to see what's inside.
If you want, grab some sapphires on the way out.
Dogs! Dogs! All of you, pig asshole dog fuckers! I'll find you. I'll skin you alive.
Go, men - and get me what I want. The night out has just begun!
I have root. There's two Gensec alarm boxes we need to disable, get to them and cut the wire.
Alright, this is where the van will drop you off.
Chopper's headed out, but stay cool - it'll be back. Look for more loot in the forest. And stay safe.
Ok guys. Let's go in. Quiet or loud, you can kill this guy any way you want.
The drill should be finished soon. I'm trying to get through to my pilot...
Don't be careful. But be fast!
Come on, stop playing with your little dick cop friends. Find the third pallet, you poes.
... now you're just showing off!
We need the ship's comm frequency. Likely on one of these terminals. Search them!
Mendoza's not going to like that outcome. But we should. Well done. Go get paid.
They're trying to shut them down!
Vault's not here. OK, keep searching.
Jesus fucking Mugabe. Look at this. Fucking pallet broke! You're going to have to bag all the spilled loot, get it back to the pallet.
Seems to be keys to an airplane.
OK that's our guy. Get the loot into the vehicle.
Seven bags!
We have half of needed fuel.
Fuck me, there's a reference to a "classified informant" here. I fucking knew it.  I'll keep digging.
You can't let them kill the power, it'll slow everything down!
There's no way back now.
Cover me while I work!
They're on to us like a bumper sticker!
That's 13 bags!
Well done, Dallas. Head to the van and get out of there.
Okay, cop switchboard lit up. Think someone must've caught sight of you. Get ready!
FBI in disarray. A lot of people about to get called into their bosses' office. Mendoza crippled and we're about to get paid. Nice burn, folks.
Uhh.. ok. But next time I'm sounding the alarm.
Hey, I got your escape driver coming in by boat. Head over to the small water access area near the river.
Guys! There's another closet door!
Guys! The power! Keep it on!
Get the server, without it everything fails!
Almost had it, but...nevermind. I gotta bail. I still get my cut, right?
And it was the right thing not to mess with Hector here - playing with fire would have gotten us burned.
They are about to blow, stand back!
I am John Henry Simmons. If you want to know more... We should talk. I might have something of interest, if you don't mind a little political intrigue...
PAYDAY is this week which means the currency's here now. Which means we are too.
Plane is on the ground. Now get the loot into it.
Hector's worried... We're too far away from the coke in this chopper. Once you're on the ground get to the coke, signal his courier, and load it on to the pick-up boat.
Snipers are being brought in, people.
Thank you. I see the fireworks. On our way!
Three more, at least!
Guys the tiara is probably in a safe or on display somewhere...
Oh. The best room in the safe house. The vault.
Alright, connect me again.
Head inside the room and go through with the drug deal.
Got it! The casino manager's code.
Hurry!
Smoke?
I got it. Hoisting it your way.
Down stairs!
We need to put the Commissar in a wooden box. Not stay in one ourselves. Move!
Industrial, high-pressure water pump used by nearby timber mill. If we're lucky, and the right wagon lands near it, we can use it to fill the vault.
One of BFD's coolant tanks is empty. She needs that water, guys. Grab a refill from the bathrooms!
The game is on, motherfucker!
My accomplice will assist you. He's waiting.
Damn it! The bastards have filled the room with gas to stop us. Gang, be quick and find a way to shut it off!
There's a slot for the keycard. My guess is just put it in and see what happens...
Escape is ready. Van is in place, engine running.
The bird is inbound with the skyhook pieces. Pick-up target is the street.
...I... Yeah, OK it's a goddamn ambush, strap on your guns folks!
Over here!
What's taking so long!?
Fix that pool I want to take a swim.
Hurry! Cops are already on their way!
Guys, don't keep them waiting. Get in there.
Now pop the manhole! We're getting out through the sewers!
That goat has live current running through it! Disable the power!
Better get moving boys, the longer it takes the more cops are going to show up!
... Flying as fast as I can.
And how much will it cost you? Shall we say... 18 bucks?
I want to send a clear message to the FBI and the whoring Mendozas. You can contribute.
Nevermind him. Are we going to unpack these crates?
Yeah. So we have our work cut out for us...
We have information about the Mendoza cashflow. Over $100 million from their American operations. We want to send a message - their money and their weapons are null and void.
The road is a perfect drop-zone. Putting your cage there.
OK, I'm in position!
Get a keycard and swipe it through the time locks. Check civvies for cards.
Did I just hear a present falling from a tree? Seems to be more of them stuck in there. Find 'em, crack 'em open.
Down there!
Look for a circuit breaker to get the power back up.
Hey, man! Careful with my hardware!

He's going to drop off the pieces for a skyhook. You gotta bolt together an aluminum cage, load it and then send up a cable on a balloon. Plane flies right over, grabs the cable and - whoosh! - off it goes.
OK, pull over here, and get your masks on.
Hey! They fucked my fucking car!!
Four left now!
Winston won't be happy!
Three gents eh? Come right in!
All right. There's one of the marked closets.
Get the cash bagged!
Keep moving the crane. Can't drop it there.
The customer is about a minute away.
It's a trap! Either you defuse these C4s or you get the hell outta there!
Ho ho ho, bitches!
Hey, two minutes, we have two more minutes until the pick-up car! Not much longer!
OK. Second act in our little drama - get the vault open.
(sings) "They're the gang that broke the bank at Monte Carlo". Outstanding!
You need to answer that pager fast, otherwise they'll sound the alarm. Just say something reassuring.
Caustic basic reaction is now added. OK you got any soda around? Add it.
That's it! Now put all the goats in it!
And what would you like as a side? Uh... sausage patties? We got 'em!
And expect best quality Russia Kalashnikovs - very good! Very fine.
Aight, four!
25 thousand, halfway guys.
Ok, this is the bank. I advise casing the place. Then hit the vault however you want. There's usually a security room so be cautious.
Don't hesitate - just jump!
If you're planning on sticking around for extra loot, that crowbar will do the trick.
Something's fucked up there. Pyro guys, you gotta deal with it.
Chopper's here, get out! Get out!
And... The bank is dark to us. Good work, crew.
Alright, we're close. Get him to the top of the tower on your right!
That's good enough for the roof.
Shoot these fuckers!
That door looks like it's made of balsa, shoot the lock of that thing.
Alright! He'll bring it over here so we can inspect it.
With you in a minute.
Fuck me, we needed those cooks. I'm going with chloride.
This will throw a monkey wrench in the security works.
I'll get in touch with the senator's people and talk 'em into buying the paintings from us.
I think it would be nice to blow the roof off this mall!
You managed to unlock the outer panic room door, so the lance shouldn't take as long!
That's it. Now you can get the hell out of there, or head back and snag more Murky loot.
It seems to have worked. You should be able to start the scanning-process now.
Put the product in the car...
We're looking good... Looking good.
You clever bastards, you'll get around them using those tunnels.
OK, the cops, they just stepped up their efforts. Tougher units incoming!
Those snipers have me pinned down. Can you take them out?
There's one!
Okay. Now help your friend Locke. Light a flare. Show me where the money is.
Haha, you read my mind, guys. I do want that briefcase.
Get away from the gate! Fast!
I bet you've always wanted to punch that judgemental bastard Santa Claus! Now is your chance!
You've come to the wrong neighbourhood, motherfuckers!
They're in the house!
That's one of the mobsters. Sneak or kill: Your choice.
... cover me! They're tearing me to pieces!
Gang, stop standing around, and get to the escape point. Follow the blue containers!
For fucks' sake! Lads! The power!
Nice! That's the money you sent ahead. OVERKILL thanks you!
... when it's done, we'll give you what you want.
Sorry. Procedure. What was your name again?
Who is this? Who the fuck are you?
Prepare for a rough landing, guys!
Come on, you kaks! Strap the money to the chopper so I can take it away!
Look up - police chopper in the sky!
Here!
Who let them in? What the fuck!?
Get the elves working on the product. Just holler at them.
Shit!
I can't fucking believe you're making me do this shit, Bain...
You heard what Locke said, guys. Into the boat and let's get out of here.
The wheel stopped on the dozer again. Watch out guys!
I loved chemistry in high school. By that, I mean I love stuff being blown up. Good work!
Hey, you gotta stay alert. Hey! Hello..?
Alright, just park the car in that container, and walk away!
I'm going as fast as I can!
Few plans survive first contact with the enemy. You adapted well, and showcased an impressive capacity for violence. Enjoy your PAYDAY. I will contact you again once things cool down.
The wheel has stopped. It says drills. I got no clue.
Good, that should get rid of the gas. You can most likely enter the room now.
You need to deal with the power box to use the ladder!
There's the boat. Hop in, my good friends! Let us take her for gentle cruise.
OK, time to stop dancing.
Alright, I'm at the spot!
Dammit! The plane missed the cable. Alright. Still time for another pass. Stand by.
Keep firing and I can get the gate open!
Pull over here. There's the warehouse up ahead. Let's do this.
Hector wants proof we didn't just swipe the cash.

We've got your money right here. The info is in the safe. I'll open it. No funny shit or you die.
In 1957, Eisenhower said that plans are worthless. Eisenhower never robbed a bank.
Placed, as per your request.
I like that.
Then you can go for their bank and burn all their money. Leaving them nothing.
What the fuck... Cops!
Get over here!
What are you waiting for?
Put the product in the car!
Who the hell do you think you are!?
Sons of bitches!
This won't end well for you, suckers!
It's the clowns! It's the fucking clowns from the news!
You doin' over there!?
Blast these fools! Do it now!
Yo yo yo, wassup?
Put the delivery in the car!
I know things are hectic and you are very busy, but would you mind getting the detonator onto the charges?
Ah! There it is! Now, please, out of the airlock and into the inner complex!
The inner complex is nothing to be scared of.
Ahhh, if any sound is sweeter than that of an opening vault it is that of bagging loot. You are producing a symphony for my ears!
Maybe I should've studied this ancient stuff more. Could the curse be true? Ah, it's just old shit worth money to me.
Almost open. Remember, you deal with the radars, and I will prepare the helicopter.
Ah kak, they know we're trying to fuck off. They're going all in! Hold steady, friends!
He only had a week left on his contract.
Ahhh, he was my friend. Well, what can you do?
That was our chaplain. You guys are stone cold.
He was my chomma. Shit happens though, right?
If I know them, and I know them, trust me on that, they'll have bulldozers up ahead. So get ready for those shits, yeah.
It's simplicity itself, friends. Just press the button of the vault you want to open. Just be sure it actually contains something.
Just press the button. You can understand that, yeah?
That's the first pallet. All right, good. Now, onto the second.
Friends! I am here and in position! Please, when the opportunity allows, take the straps and attach them to that wonderful stack of money.
I left a case of thermal paste for you down there. Make sure you grab it.
Look around for a ladder. I'm sure that with energy properly applied to a search you will profit. For sure.
Get up on the roofs, friends. Maybe you will see things clearer up there, yeah? You'll probably need a ladder to get up.
Oh, ese, you're over-delivering! Very nice!
Shit, the policia is here!
... drop 'em!
... waste 'em!
I see one!
What's taking so long?
Ey, I don't have all day...
What the fuck's happening!?
That is all, good.
These bags look pretty roughed up... What have you been doing with them?
Kill 'em all!
Die! DIE!
You're gonna die ugly.
There he is!
There's one!
You guys are lucky, I'm feeling generous...
... then you get what you came here for.
So what you're telling me is, if I have this straight, what you're saying, is that you ain't interested in investing in a pager business?

Eh, I'll say it for you: you didn't come here only to save me, now did ya? No, you're here for the custom built bike, am I right or am I right? I'll help you. I owe you that much, but you'll have to get me the parts I need.
Hello? Don't go without me!
Fuck! I don't wanna die today!
Not like this, not like this!
All right, I'm gonna need my special tools to put the bike together. They should be in their usual place in the workshop inside one of the toolboxes.
Oh, yeah. Wait. You're gonna need this blowtorch to get inside.
Where's my god damn protection?!
Ya gotta be a player, but ya gotta rig the game, man!
Got one supermodel on my D, second supermodel mixing me a mighty fine G & T. King looks over and winks.
And I don't wanna see no bills written up for this.
Come on, we need more than that!
What the hell are you doing here?
You better hurry up and fix that leakage
Who the fuck are those people?
This is Captain Rogers of the MPDC. We got a call from Gensec. Seems they got some concerns about what's happening there. I'm dispatching some uniformed officers to make sure everything's OK.
Stow the loot in the ceiling vent marked by the Inside Man.
Alright, that's it for the concert. Time to de-mask and blend in with the crowd. If all goes to plan, you'll be able to stroll right out the front door. Good luck.
Ok, so maybe blending in isn't our style. Sending the helicopter now!
The roof is not an option, We're going to have to "improvise"... slightly.
Well, there goes plan A. Glad the crowd didn't hear any of that.
Great. Now, grab the loot. Let's finish this caper quiet like.
Delaware Popcorn!
Capitol Hill Candy!
Remember to stash that loot in the vents. I got them marked for you.
Seven bucks! All right!
More C4. Almost there. Keep looking.
Great. Now go blast that obstruction. It's your way out.
Christ, LA's wrecked. Rubble everywhere.
The trucks are here somewhere. Vlad's guys will be too, so watch your fire.
Find those trucks! And don't shoot Vlad's guys if any of them are still around.
You'll never carry those out. Gonna need a transport, and a way out. Give me a minute, I'll find something.
Damn, place is wrecked. Still looking. Hang in there.
I'm still looking. Damn, LA is smoked. Hold them off.

Gensec's overland armored convoys employ a lot of ex-military types, providing firepower and muscle, and they move everything from little Jimmy's favorite baseball card to the Crown Jewels. We got a line on a convoy moving into D.C. Let's see what we can get.
Great job! I'm sending the boat, keep looting!
It's open! Let's see what we got!
This is interesting. Military blueprints in a Gensec transport. I'll look into it.
OK, guys, here they come. Get that crane moving!
That's the server room. Get inside and get me connected.
I'm in. Hold on, guys - I need a little time.
Yes, that is a giant piggy bank. No, I haven't lost my mind.
Even diamond bits break! You're gonna need the spare parts to get it going again.
There were spare drill bits in the piggy bank.
Don't ask me where I got that thumb. Now verify identification from the security consoles. Shouldn't be a problem.
One down, one to go.
Got it! Now get back to the vault and enter the code.
Got the code. Get back to the vault.
Pick up the thermite. That's our way into the vault.
They're the keys for the doors inside the vault. Good find.
Not only did you boost a crapload of cash, this caper wiped millions off Benevolent's share price. Great work!
This will forever be a Red Letter day for the criminal community. The day the PAYDAY gang broke the Benevolent.
That's the address! We've got what we need. Get back to the van and we can get out of here.
Shit, the cops are here!
They're coming from the east, by the forest.
Good, now set up the connection.
Sorry guys, he says this ain't the one. I'll be back in a few so you can give me the working one.
OK, that's the clubhouse. Bikers' got the address we need. Sneak in.
OK, this is a fight - they will destroy the intel!
Get the power to the server back on!
Got connection. Keep working.
OK, chopper is coming in to pick up that Fusion Engine.
Sorry guys, he says this ain't the one. The chopper will be back in a few so you can get another one over here, hopefully the right one.
Blackhawk! Blackhawk coming down! Gun up team!
Cash job in the branch bank. Let's hit this thing. Should be a good win.
We might have a very valuable object in this bank. I have insurance papers backing that up.

I got word one of the Harvest & Trustee banks just had a big run on safe deposit rentals from a teller I used to uh, speak to, socially. I think we should get into the vault and strip those boxes bare... You with me?
OK this is your standard job only it's gold-plated, if you take my meaning.
OK, standard bank hit, only we're going for the gold drop off day. Gotta remain liquid, right?
Everyone, you know how it's done. My guy dropped the thermal drill in the parking lot, so grab that before you make your move inside. Some surveillance would be smart.
They're coming into the bank!
Getting pretty unpleasant out there. You guys sure you wanna stick around?
They're in the bank!
Hold them in position.
Close... Come on folks... Getting there.
They had no chance at all. I don't think the National Guard could have stopped you.
The workshop is where you'll find the tools. That's what the mechanic said.
The mechanic told you to go to the bunker and get the seat for him.
Remember: the mechanic said something about a bunker, and that you would find a seat for the bike there.
Excellent, that's a part in the bag. Bring it back to the mechanic.
That's some fine loot they stashed in there, but it's ours now. How do we get it out?
Ride, boys and girls, ride!
We've got cops on the way, so don't dawdle. Find the C4! Check the guard room.
Seven
How much did you win? Can we all retire?
Come on, guys. Get the plans scanned and faxed. Do it in IT.
Let me check. Room...
OK, first things first, look for the gear case.
All right. Head to reception, find a terminal and download the guest list.
Our All You Can Eat buffet is now open, and I wanted to make sure that you knew.
You won't find a better New York steak anywhere, including New York.
All You Can Eat, remember. Just 18 bucks.
Fill his glass. Once he downs that, well... he's going to lose interest in the slots. Follow him, and get his keycard.
That's it, buddy. Drink up.
Opening the vault needs a three digit code. Each digit is held by a manager, and each is in a computer briefcase. We need that code. Find them.
That's all three digits for the code. Head to the vault, let's see if they work.
All right, snatch up those winch parts.
Nice! Next, we're going to signal the blimp, and for something like that we need a big signal. A fireworks display! Find them!
Nice. Now light the fusepaper and...
Start the winch and it will move BFD into position. Don't let the cops stop it!
Winch isn't working, crew. Fix it!
See that guitar case over there? That's your gear.
The guest list, guys. Get it from reception and we can see who's in our room.
Now! After him. Wait til he's alone.
Okay gamblers. Let's get gambling.
Kill every one of those thugs, gang.
I'm looking at the manager's file. Chances are he's wearing a black suit.
Looks like the manager is losing a bit on top. Look for the balding guy.
Alright, I got it! The storage room is now unlocked. Go get the car keys.
The keys are in the storage room. Grab 'em!
I'm jealous you're going to get to drive this beast.
Now the fun part - steal a car! I'll blast the road - take cover!
Cops are on the way. Time is important, so hustle!
Check the manager's office. Look for the IT guys name. Come on, come on!
See that nice big hole? Drive through it, and hit the gas!
Nice, I'll detonate these. You just be ready with the cars.

Teuer autos is our objective here. We're going to hit their dealership late in the evening. Should be quiet, not many civilians. They're a high-end joint. Deal in importing high-performance supercars from Europe and Japan. Those cars are a work of engineering beauty. And they're expensive - we're talking the price of a house in Georgetown here.
A rare job. Hit the Teuer dealership. Boost the new models.
Pull over here. Alright gang. Let's do this.
Keep pushing forward, gang!
Holy...! They rigged the boxes with C4! Defuse them!
Hurry up and get back to the chopper so we can secure the BCI tech.
No broken legs? Good. Head into the forest and find that plane. My guess is the pilot will be nearby. Get him someplace safe and we'll evac him by air. Move out!
Alright, chopper's here. Bring the pilot to it!
Chopper's on the scene. Get him there. Just pray he doesn't reach for the controls.
There goes the chopper, but don't worry - it'll be back. In the meantime, let's see if you can track down some more of those presents.
Was that a coke-filled present falling from a tree? Christmas really is the time of miracles.
The night's not so silent. Think I heard another present hit the ground. Find it!
Oh man, the pilot just went down again. Wake that old wino up!
The old drunk is on the ground again. Get him to his feet.
Chopper's headed for the lumber yard - be there!
Chopper's headed for the crash site. Get ready!
Chopper sees the flare. He's on his way. One minute.
Great. That's keycard one. We need to find one more.
Good work. Just need to find one more keycard.
Well, the front door's closed.  No surprise. Look for another way in.
The front is shut tight. Take a walk around. Find another way in.
We're inside. Good. Next, gonna need a couple of keycards. Smart money would be on them being indoors.
You took care of both guards. Don't have to worry about the cameras anymore.
This is it, gang. They're throwing everything they have in to this. Get out of there!
Guys, you gotta get into the dockyard.
This is one of the ship Control Rooms. Computers can be used for entering GPS targets, or you might find Moretta's comm frequency. There could also be a keycard or radio here.
Hey! These terminals likely have the comm frequency for the Moretta. We're gonna need it before long.
The frequency ain't here. The control room is across the dock - maybe check there.
There she is. The Moretta. No access here, though. Get it to dock 3B.
You're looking for keycards. The buildings are your best bet.
You need to find keycards. My guess is that the buildings are your best chance.
She's moving. But not fast. This will take some time. Stay hidden, guys. Lie low. Or, if you want, look around for extra loot.
She stopped! Get on deck and and search the containers!
That's a start.
Alright. Let's try this again.
Damn! The containers got locked when the alarm was triggered. Gonna have to drill them.
What the? Ah fuuu... Containers were locked when the alarm tripped. Drill them!
Ship database. Should have... Got it! Comm frequency for the Moretta. This is it! Now find a radio. Let's call the Captain.
These wagons might have something valuable in them. Maybe check them out?
You can use that keycard in the control room. Just swipe it, open the dock.
Guys! Use the keycards in the dock control rooms. Get the dock gate open.
Gate won't open with you standing on it, genius. Clear the area!
Come on, gang. Patch me into the radio.
Moretta is berthed and ready for you, clowns.
Ah, it's empty! Find another one.
That's it. Now haul those parts out of there.
They have no clue you are there. Now keep looking for those keycard.
Still don't know you're there. Look for the keycard.
You're keeping it quiet. Great. Remember - you need the keycard.
All's quiet still. Good work. Stay hidden while the Moretta docks.
We have to blow that gate. Get the C4 on it.
Away from the gate! Hustle it!
We still need to get that ship to the berth. Ummm... OK, I got it. Hack the ship control terminal. Keep the cops off it.
Gang, I can't stress how important electricity is to computers!
Lucky that you found the manifest. Now we know which containers to drill!
That manifest you picked up will point us to the right containers.
Gang, don't forget to crack those containers. Drill 'em!
Lets see what we have here.
Come on, let's see what you got.
Good job! Finding extra loot always makes me happy.
Search around for a ladder. You'll need it for the wagons.
Look around for a ladder. You need it to search the wagons. Maybe it's still attached to one of them.
You might wanna scout the wagons for some extra loot. And keep your eyes open for C4. You're gonna need it later. Should be in one of the crates.
Check other wagons for extra loot. And C4. Look for that too.
Cops pulled the hose. Get it back on!
Dammit! They yanked the hose. Get there, get it back on.
Deploy C4 inside the vault! Then get ready.
Explosive's in. And...
There's a boat on the lake. A zip-line can get you across.
Clear the path. Clear the trees!
It's filling up fast, crew. Just keep it going. When it's full, plant the charge and enjoy the show.
Keep the water flowing, gang. Just a little more. Then just rig it, and let hydrodynamics do its job.
Wagon's not gonna crack itself open. Dip that C4 in!
Two ways to go about this, gentlemen. Go loud - you know how to do that. But if you're hoping to raise your game, look for two keycards and unlock the vault. Car trunks are a good place to look.
There it goes. The vault is open. It's all yours, gang.
Bag of cash, great. But let's pay off that asshole first. Yellow wall by the auto-repair shop. Don't worry, we'll find and deal with him later.
Stand by, gang. Organizing an exit. Hold the line!
There must be keycards around the place. They can help you get in quiet.
Vault keycard. It gets half the job done. Swipe it in the reader, and then track down the second card.
Remember to go grab the thermal drill.
Good afternoon. Roberts bank. How can I help you?
This is Randolph. Roberts Bank is happy to serve you.
The plane will collect the cage from the parking lot, so get these bags there and get building.
I admire your attitude. Your dedication will pay off.
Our pilot has ditched his plane. That asshole! Time to adapt, gang!
Someone alerted the cops. No matter. We got what we came for.
Broadsword calling Danny Boy. Time to drop that skyhook cage. Over.
Plane is coming in hot. He'll collect from the roof. Make sure everything is ready.
It's a piss poor location, but the pilot will collect the cage from the street. Be ready.
Look around. The codes must be written somewhere. I can't stall them forever!
Ah, here we are. Right in front of me. 674523.
I guess we better do what the little hood rat bastard says. It's tough to be a criminal in a town as rotten as this.
Shooters on the roof. Watch out!
It's the Feds! What the hell! They were waiting for us!
Just saw another civilian stroll into the street. Deal with them.
Gang, Gensec truck. Hey, it might be carrying a keycard. You know what to do. Get at them.
This is a new tactic. I'm seeing cops placing tripmines in the parking lot. Don't let them get that shit set up.
It's about to get hot down there, gang. They're dropping grenades.
Eight bags. Out-fucking-standing.
Keep an eye on all entry points, especially the ladders.
There's an access hatch to the sewers over by the gas station. Go there, and get down.
See that drive thru window at the side of the bank? There's a manhole there to the sewers. Get down there.
Cash is out of town and you are in the clear. Reminds me of the bridge job way back when.
Remember the plan. Get the keycards, keep the civilians in check and set off no alarms.
The cops just shut of the drill!
The drill is out - damn cops!
The vault has two security routers protecting it and you need to shut them both down. Easily done if you patch me into them directly. Look for them mounted on the walls.
Look on the walls for the router boxes.
C'mon guys, find me those security boxes. Check the walls.
I'll have the system down in a bit.
That's about halfway done.
You're all done. Get to the roof and signal the chopper if you're ready to leave!
That laptop had one part of the vault code. There are two more around there somewhere.
Get ready for extraction. Chopper is 4 minutes out.
Get up to the roof and light a flare to signal pickup.
There's the second one.
And another one.
Something in the cafeteria and it isn't Jeff Vader. It looks like a glowing LCD display.
There's something electronic and glowing in the Admin Office.
Go check the Velvet Room for a laptop. Just don't stick to the walls.
The Velvet Room. Search it for a PC ASAP.
See if someone in Management forgot their computer.
I think I see a PC in one of the meeting rooms through the secruty camera.
That vault is just waiting to be emptied guys. Use the keycard, then enter the code.
Might want to pick up the pace gang.The keycard and code are all you need.
Great work, now let's see that glittering carbon.
Use a glass-cutter. Don't break the glass!
You found a second vault?
Another vault. Didn't expect that.
Keep working guys.
Bag and secure. You know the routine.
That's half of 'em.
Quit messing around and get out of there.
Damn! They locked out the code. Need a backup plan.
The code you have has been disabled, but I think the system has a master code. Let me do some digging.
That was the wrong sequence, now the system is locked unless you find the master code!
There goes the alarm!
Damn, they know you're there now for sure.
That's one, find the next!
Great! I'm in.
Cops are tryint to stop us. Defend those routers while I work!
Blues are trying to pull the plug on us, make sure they fail!
Protect the routers.
OK,I'm done here!
Go find Ralph Garnet and take that keycard from his priviledged-ass-self.
The CFO has the master code guys. Find him!
You still need to find the master code!
C'mon guys, get that guy to the roof.
Need to hurry gang.
I'll crack this guy like an egg and have that code for you shortly.
Swipe Ralph's card before entering the code.
zero
two
four
five
seven
nine
Let me repeat
Don't screw this up. The code's...
Probably worth a fortune.
Get that red diamond and this'll be a double Payday.
Great job keeping it quiet everyone. Almost worth shouting from the rooftops.
Textbook execution people.
No cops on the drill, guys!
Keep the cops off the machinery, guys!
Ok guys, Get after that gold!
Close down on that truck. Get that gold!
All right, the truck is through there. Grab the C4 from the bin and blow that door.
Remember to grab the C4. That is your way through the door.
Crew, bring it down. Perhaps a little force will do it.
Guys, the safe! Get the drill on it - pronto!
Nice. Out in the yard, I have a container ready to stash the gold. Number 61. Get it there!
Now the helicopter won't see where we load the containers.
Great! Now we can get out of here. Get to the escape. Follow the blue containers!
Close the door in their faces. Blast the gas!
Ok guys. I'm opening container 57 remotely. Get ready to run.
Just get out of there!
The helicopter will see where we load our containers. Gotta deal with that.
Police chopper is over you. We can't let them see which container we use.
The van can stay up there, but we still need what's in it. Plant the C4 on the doors!
All right, nice work! Now get to the container. Drop the gas can there.

Murkywater's been moving stuff through DC by convoy for months. I've resisted hitting these til we got a shot at a big prize. Here it is. Gold bullion. Got a "diversion" on the Woodrow set up to get it where we want it, then we're gonna seperate an armored truck from an armed convoy. Once it's isolated, hit it and boost that sweet bling. Au yeah.
We're ambushing a convoy down by the docks. The cargo is gold. The convoy is Murkywater. Questions?
That's it, the hidden train yard. Use this opportunity to scout the area. The place is heavily guarded by Murkies and cameras, so we can't afford to make any mistakes.
You really need to find a keycard to get that door open. Come on.
Excellent, you found a keycard. Now, head back to the train and open that sucker.
Get back to the security gate and use the thermite.
Murkywater like their technology, so they should have some kind of mobile command center nearby. See what you can find.
There must be something we can use to get past the vault security system.
Just what we needed! Plug that hard drive in and I'll take care of it. That vault should be opened in no time.
Maybe that equipment will come in handy later, so hold on to it.
Excellent, we got what we came for. Get over to the escape area and secure the EMP.
Excellent, we got the EMP secured. I won't blame you if you want to get some extra loot before you escape. Up to you.
Why not go back and get some of that juicy loot? I'll make it worth your time.
Listen up, gang. I'm sending in a boat to pick you up. Look for the small water access near the river.
Listen up, gang. Twitch is coming in with the van. He will come from the upper bridge side.
Have you searched through the whole train yard?
Don't get lazy, gang. Search the whole train yard if needed.
It might be worth to check the maintenance tunnels.
The area isn't too big. You should be able to move around and search all corners of the whole train yard.
Looks like the EMP isn't here, but there might be some other valuable loot for us. You can either check it now or come back later.

I'm not gonna lie; we are taking a huge risk by double-crossing Akan, but I believe this is the right choice. First thing is getting the EMP bomb that is being transported by Murkywater. They will be making a scheduled stop. That will be our chance. Get in quietly, find the EMP, then get out of there. You need to do this by stealth, so dress the part.
More money in our pockets and it should also win us some favor with Locke.
Get into docks. There'll be security, so stay hidden and stay quiet.
OK, now look around. We need to tag the truck headed for Washington. Look around for clues. Containers, terminals, any records. Find the right one, and tag it.
Getting a nice clear signal. Time to leave, guys. I hope you tagged the right truck.
They've seen you! The trucks are moving out. Alright, we need a Plan B. Lemme think.
The trucks are on the move. Someone saw you! OK, time for another plan.
OK, the database is split into two. I'm getting the first one now.
OK. Whole database is recovered. No point hanging around - get back to the boat.
That shitty network will transfer the databases faster if you can keep the cops from pulling the plug on it.
Those containers have cargo. That might help you eliminate the wrong trucks.
One of these is the truck carrying the voting machines to Washington. When you think you know which one it is, get the tracker on it and we can move on.
Pier 39. Find the truck that has the voting machines. It will be bound for Washington. Figure out which one it is, slap on the tracker and get the hell out. Keep it quiet.
You're in. Now, the target is the voting machines. They're likely in shipping crates, so look around for those.
That certainly looks like one of the voting machines. When you're ready to kill democracy, start the hack. Make sure no-one sees you.
Looks like one of our machines. Start the hack, and then keep the feds off it.

OK, I've got an idea. I can change the hack so it looks like we were here doing this for McCendrick's rival, Mayor Schwartz. The blame can be passed on to her. If there's gonna be a scandal, let's make it a scandal we can use!
Here's the new plan. I'm altering the hack to make it look like this whole enterprise is for Mayor Schwartz instead. It's a dirty trick, but this is politics.
Job's nearly done, guys. Just one more thing. Get the camera footage from the security room. I wanna make sure they didnt film anything we don't want them to.
You need to find where the camera footage is kept. Move it, guys.
A fighting retreat back to the van, guys. Let's get out of here.
Almost there... Almost there.
That was a superb display of stealth. You guys are made of shadows. The machines are hacked, the votes are flooding in and it is a landslide for The Elephant's man. God bless democracy!

Great work! The hacked machines have made it look like the Mayor's people were behind this. Even if an enquiry exonerates her, the papers are hurling so many buckets of shit at the Mayor that she's finished. And The Elephant? Well, his man is picking out new furniture for City Hall. Great work, gang!
Damn, that cheap piece of shitty Russian crap scrambler crashed. Get it going again.
Get inside the vault, gang. See what's inside!
I got you an escape van, just outside the main entrance!
Close. So close.
Alright, got it. Here we go
Alright guys, the trucks might leave any second. Find out which one contains the voting machines and put the GPS tracker on it. There must be something around here that can give you a clue.
OK team this is it. The trucks look like they're getting ready to leave - so hurry and find the one carrying the container. GPS is ready to go. Move out.
Remember the other trucks are ours! But we still want our loot back, use them to disctract the cops away from the ballot machines.
Take care of the cops in the convoy, and lets open the trucks up!
The hacking device you supposedly fixed is jammed again. You need to reboot it.
Find the truck from the harbor and get inside. Reprogram the machines without anyone seeing you. Hit the Gensec van to smokescreen what happened. Cops in this town aren't the sharpest, after all.
Looks like the scrambler software just crashed. You'll have to restart it!
This vault is full of cash! You'll have to decide how much you can get away with.
OK, the escape vehicle's ready for you in the garage.
The surveillance operator is down, those cameras shouldn't bother you anymore!
But we can't just do that - we need cover that up with a much bigger crime, so just take down the bank in the meantime. I know, it's a little excessive, but then again we're good at excessive.
OK we can rest easy - no votes are getting cast today. And we got cash to boot. Good win, and good times.
By the time they get new ones out there it'll be too late - and there will be no voting in this district.
The chopper is one minute away.
The van leaves in one minute. Wrap it up!
Secure as much loot as you can. The escape vehicle is leaving in three minutes.
Your ride will be there in about five minutes.
Hurry up, guys! The escape vehicle is leaving in five minutes.
The escape will be there in eight minutes.
The escape vehicle will be there in ten minutes.
